Program: Discovery
Title: Comets - the bringers of life
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwr7
Last Broadcast Date: 25 October 1996
Comets, why they could help scientists explain the origins of the solar system. A report on comets and how some of the material they carry could have helped form our Sun and even bring water to the earth. Also in the programme, what makes drug addicts slaves to their habits and the unlikely start of the world's largest network of science museums. Show less